Package makesudokus.logic.algorithms.crook

Class Cell

  • java.lang.Object
    • makesudokus.logic.algorithms.crook.Cell
  • public class Cell
extends java.lang.Object

    A data container class for a single Sudoku Cell used by the Crook's algorithm solver.

    Has private variables for markups and is aware whether or not the number it contains is known or not

    • Constructor Detail

      • Cell

        public Cell​(int digit)

        Constructor for the Cell data structure.

        The digit parameter dictates, whether or not the number in the cell is known when the Cell object is created. Then sets the boolean "known" accordingly. 1-9 means the number is known and 0 means unknown.
        Parameters:
        digit - The known initial digit of the cell. 0 if unknown.

      • crossout

        public void crossout​(int digit)
        Crosses out one slot in the markups. In other words, if this method gets an integer n, it will cross out the boolean representing n from the markups.
        Parameters:
        digit - The number to crossout
